article.headline: Portland State 93, UC Davis 61
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Paul Hafford came off the bench to score a career-high 27 points, leading Portland State to a 93-61 victory over UC Davis on Tuesday. Hafford connected on 6-of-11 from 3-point range for the Vikings (8-4), who remained unbeaten on their home floor this season. Dupree Lucas added 16 points for Portland State and Juma Kamara had 11. Vince Oliver led UC Davis (1-8) with 14 points. Rommell Marentez scored 11 points for the Aggies before fouling out. Portland State broke open a close game late in the first half, grabbing a 39-27 halftime lead when Hafford hit two consecutive 3-pointers with less than a minute left. Another Hafford 3-pointer capped a 7-0 Viking run to start the second half. The Aggies did not get closer than 14 points the rest of the way.
